    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-05-01T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-05-01T18:00:00-05:00" n="43"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d43">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">851G.00/5–146: Circular telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Certain <gloss type="to">Diplomatic and Consular Officers</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="39" xml:id="d43fn1">At Bangkok, Batavia, London, Nanking, Paris,
                        Singapore, and The Hague.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-05-01T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 1, 1946—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>French Vietnam conference Dalat temporarily suspended for study conflicting views
                    re Cochinchina. Vietnam officials hope for future clouded by doubts French will
                    abide by their agreements. French pessimistic re outcome. Vietnam demands
                    cessation hostilities Cochinchina, release political internees, establishment
                    armistice commission and political freedom Cochinchina. French counter-offer
                    special committee study French-Vietnam incidents throughout Indochina. French
                    now hold Dalat conference merely preliminary and results must have Paris
                    approval.</p>
                <p>Consul Saigon observes<note n="40" xml:id="d43fn2">Telegram 130, April 30, 1946,
                        3 p.m., not printed. In it Consul Reed mentioned that Ho Chi Minh had
                        stressed to him at Hanoi “utmost necessity of interesting American capital
                        and employing American technicians in Vietnam.” (851G.00/4–3046)</note>
                    French maneuvers propaganda to force withdrawal Chinese troops Tonkin and
                    delaying tactics Dalat conference compatible with possibility French planning
                    military coup when Chinese withdraw.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
